&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Upstream approaches to help seniors age at home: the view from Silicon Valley&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The Columbia Aging Center presents Nirav R. Shah, MD, MPH, Senior Scholar, Clinical Excellence Research Center, Stanford University&lt;br /&gt;
Registration required: &lt;a href="https://tinyurl.com/CACNirav" target="_blank"&gt;https://tinyurl.com/CACNirav&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
In this Columbia Aging Center seminar (aging.columbia.edu), Nirav Shah will talk about technology and aging. While new technologies and Artificial Intelligence have changed how we live, how we work, and how we socialize &amp;ndash; little has changed in health and healthcare. Yet promising technologies will facilitate aging at home, improved access to care, and reduced disparities, along with nascent opportunities to improve prevention and healthcare at scale. We present a framework for identifying, selecting, and implementing such supporting structures for healthy longevity.&lt;/p&gt;

