&lt;h2&gt;Navigating HOT Moments: Before, During, &amp;amp; After Class&amp;nbsp;(for Faculty)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A 75-minute workshop for Columbia Faculty.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regardless of course topic or content,&amp;nbsp;HOT &amp;mdash; heated, offensive, or tense &amp;mdash; moments in the classroom are always a possibility. Although never fully avoidable or predictable, there are steps instructors can take to help mitigate the potential for these moments, and strategies to help better equip instructors for navigating HOT moments when they occur. Building upon material from the &lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/resources-and-technology/resources/anti-racist-pedagogy/"&gt;Anti-Racist Pedagogy in Action: First Steps resource&lt;/a&gt;, this session will help instructors identify strategies for engaging with, facilitating, and navigating HOT moments before, during, and after class.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After attending this workshop, participants should be able to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify strategies for anticipating and preparing for HOT moments before they occur&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify ways to respond to and follow up on HOT classroom moments during and after class&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access strategies to become better equipped to navigate HOT classroom moments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unable to join us for this workshop? Engage with the CTL on-demand resource: &lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/resources-and-technology/resources/navigating-hot-moments/"&gt;Navigating Heated, Offensive, and Tense (HOT) Moments in the Classroom&lt;/a&gt;. You can also schedule a &lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/faculty/offerings/consultations/"&gt;consultation&lt;/a&gt;, or find other workshops on our &lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/events/"&gt;CTL events calendar&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

