&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Yanomami Struggle&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A conversation with the Yanomami shaman and leader, Davi Kopenawa on the historical campaign for the defense of this people&amp;acute;s sovereignty and the current situation in Brazil, on the occasion of The Yanomami Struggle exhibition opening at The Shed, New York.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://theshed.org/program/262-the-yanomami-struggle"&gt;The Yanomami Struggle&lt;/a&gt; is curated by Thyago Nogueira, Instituto Moreira Salles, S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, Brazil (IMS) with the guidance of Davi Kopenawa , and organized by IMS, the Fondation Cartier pour l&amp;rsquo;art contemporain, and The Shed in partnership with the Brazilian NGOs Hutukara Associa&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o Yanomami and Instituto Socioambiental.&lt;/p&gt;
