&lt;p&gt;Columbia University&amp;#39;s Rare Book &amp;amp; Manuscript&amp;nbsp;Library (RBML) and the Oral History Archives at Columbia (OHAC) present a Curatorial Short with&amp;nbsp;Kurt Boone &amp;amp; Kimberly Springer on &amp;quot;Mass incarceration oral histories of one family&amp;rsquo;s experiences.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Often unrecognized in discourses about mass incarceration are jails and prisons as &amp;ldquo;both/and&amp;rdquo;: both sites of imprisonment and labor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;New York poet and urban culture collector &lt;a href="http://www.kurtboonebooks.com/" target="_blank"&gt;Kurt Boone&lt;/a&gt; conducted oral history interviews with eight of his family whose lives are touched by incarceration. Some were incarcerated. Others have children or parents implicated in the U.S. prison system. Still others work in law enforcement or corrections.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through this familial lens, the narrators add dimension and depth to how we listen to our loved ones&amp;rsquo; stories, construct our personal histories, and think about our country&amp;rsquo;s over-reliance on imprisonment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&amp;#39;ll discuss the motivations for the interview project, hear about challenges with interviewing family on a sensitive topic, as well as listen to a few interview clips.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To register for the event, please use this Zoom webinar link: &amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://columbiauniversity.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_UhdmZ5isRkOauOEveLlhsg" target="_blank"&gt;https://columbiauniversity.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_UhdmZ5isRkOauOEveLlhsg&lt;/a&gt;. The event will be recorded and posted to &lt;a href="https://blogs.cul.columbia.edu/rbml/category/oral-history/" target="_blank"&gt;the oral history section&lt;/a&gt; of the RBML news website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Browse the collection&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Listen to audio and read the&amp;nbsp;interview&amp;nbsp;transcripts for this collection in Columbia University Libraries&amp;#39; online Digital Library Collection: &lt;a href="http://tiny.cc/ohac-mass-incarceration" target="_blank"&gt;http://tiny.cc/ohac-mass-incarceration&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

