&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Virtual Panel Discussion in French.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This virtual panel is part of a larger series of events on&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://maisonfrancaise.org/thinking-algeria-at-60-images-from-a-revolution"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Algeria at 60: Images from a Revolution&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Photography has been an important point of departure for the exploration of the political possibilities of images in contemporary Algeria. In this panel discussion in French, Ammar Bouras and Mourad Krinah, two leading Algerian visual artists, discuss visual culture and politics with Selma Hellal, visionary editor of Barzakh Press, whose catalog includes arresting photo journals and photographic chronicles, and Malika Rahal, a historian whose innovative writing explores the intersections of history and memory.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
