&lt;p&gt;Welcome and Introduction by:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="https://www.law.columbia.edu/faculty/anu-bradford" target="_blank"&gt;Anu Bradford&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Henry L. Moses Professor of Law and International Organization and Director of the European Legal Studies Center&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Three years ago, the European Union adopted its European Green Deal&amp;mdash;a set of ambitious goals to become climate-neutral and protect its environment. Since then, Europe has had to cope with major global challenges, from the COVID-19 pandemic to the current energy crisis stemming from the war in Ukraine. Frans Timmermans, Executive Vice President of the European Commission, who leads the Commission&amp;rsquo;s work on the European Green Deal, will discuss how Europe is keeping up with its commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
