&lt;p&gt;Are you a graduate student preparing a teaching statement for the academic job market? At this session, you will meet with CTL staff and colleagues from other departments to collectively analyze excerpts from real teaching statements. You&amp;#39;ll analyze how the instructor effectively communicates their practice and approach to teaching as well as what details make the excerpts effective or not so effective. Hearing others&amp;#39; readings of the samples will help you to write and revise your own statement by honing your critical eye.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prior to this session, participants are expected to have completed a 20-minute module on Canvas. To get started on the module, self-enroll in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Intro to the Teaching Statement&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Canvas site here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://bit.ly/3tnGgda" target="_blank"&gt;https://bit.ly/3tnGgda&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
