&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Online &amp;amp; Hybrid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This initiative&amp;rsquo;s main objective is to promote a space for debate and offer a comprehensive platform for the exchange of ideas.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This initiative&amp;rsquo;s main objective is to promote a space for debate and offer a comprehensive platform for the exchange of ideas, discussion and analysis on the current role of Latin America and the Caribbean in the global arena, as well as its implications and challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The process of continual integration in Latin America and the Caribbean and the growing role of the region as a strategic, political and trading partner in today&amp;rsquo;s world order are among the topics of unique importance to be discussed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This effort aims to bring together the main centers of thought dedicated to the study of the region&amp;rsquo;s dynamics to discuss and formulate proposals that contribute to equitable development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The event will take place alongside the Annual Period of the Ordinary Session of the United Nations General Assembly, in New York City on September 21, 22 and 23, 2022 and is aimed toward academics and figures working in the region&amp;rsquo;s political, economic and social fields.&lt;/p&gt;
