&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;J-Now: Zenger Lecture with Wendi C. Thomas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Poverty isn&amp;rsquo;t an accident, it&amp;rsquo;s a robbery. Good journalism targets the thieves.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wendi Thomas will discuss&amp;nbsp;finding justice through journalism. She will describe what it looks like to reject traditional journalism as it&amp;rsquo;s been done to marginalized communities and how MLK50 does journalism differently. She&amp;#39;ll take you from broad-minded, visionary terms down to practical matters, with a description of her&amp;nbsp;award-winning nonprofit hospital debt collection investigation and her organization&amp;#39;s coverage of the Byhalia oil pipeline.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Wendi is an award-winning journalist focused on economic and racial justice. She is the founding editor and publisher at MLK50 in Memphis, Tennessee.&lt;/p&gt;
