&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Virtual Public Outreach Session on EPA&amp;rsquo;s Office of Land and Emergency Management&amp;rsquo;s Environmental Justice (EJ) Action Plan focused on Recycling Infrastructure grant program, Recycling Education and Out&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Registration for Virtual Public Outreach Session on EPA&amp;rsquo;s Office of Land and Emergency Management&amp;rsquo;s Environmental Justice (EJ) Action Plan focused on Recycling Infrastructure grant program, Recycling Education and Outreach grant program, and Battery Recycling programs.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency&amp;rsquo;s Office of Land and Emergency Management has developed and is seeking stakeholder input on a draft EJ Action Plan. This public outreach session will focus on Recycling Infrastructure grant program, Recycling Education and Outreach grant program, and Battery Recycling programs. The goal of this session is to obtain feedback on the new Bipartisan Infrastructure Law funding opportunities and battery recycling program.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The EPA will be hosting five virtual public outreach sessions, each on a different aspect of the draft plan, to provide the public with an opportunity to submit input before the plan is finalized.&lt;br /&gt;
