&lt;p&gt;Do you use Python or R and want to expand your repertoire? &amp;nbsp;Are you a newcomer to programming who wants to start at the cutting edge, a Matlab user looking for an open-source language that won&amp;#39;t slow you down, or a veteran coder on the perpetual quest for a perfect programming language?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come to Intro to Julia for Python Users, a workshop geared towards people familiar with python who want to start working with the &lt;a href="https://julialang.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Julia programming language&lt;/a&gt;. &amp;nbsp;We will review the many syntactical similarities between Python and Julia and&amp;nbsp;then explore important Julia concepts that help speed up Pythonic Julia programs. &amp;nbsp;Basic knowledge of Python is suggested.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sponsored by Columbia University Libraries &lt;a href="https://library.columbia.edu/services/research-data-services.html"&gt;Research Data Services&lt;/a&gt;, Data Club provides a regular opportunity for those interested in analyzing data with open source computing to meet up and learn. Data Club meetups occur twice-monthly throughout the semester. Open to everyone in the Columbia community, these informal, hour-long events start with a presentation on a specific use case for Python, R, or Julia. They then open up to questions, collaborative work, and discussion. Computation occurs within a &lt;a href="http://jupyter.org"&gt;Jupyter&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href="http://colab.research.google.com/"&gt;Google Colab&lt;/a&gt; workflow, and participants of all skill levels are welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to stay informed about Data Club proceedings, please &lt;a href="https://listserv.cuit.columbia.edu/scripts/wa.exe?A0=CUL-DATA-CLUB"&gt;subscribe to the CUL-Data-Club mailing list&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Arnold A. Saltzman Institute of War and Peace Studies&amp;nbsp;presents&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The 13th Annual Kenneth N. Waltz Lecture in International Relations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barbara F. Walter, &lt;/strong&gt;University of California San Diego&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IS THE US HEADED TOWARD A SECOND CIVIL WAR?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hosted by &lt;strong&gt;Keren Yarhi-Milo,&lt;/strong&gt; Director, Saltzman Institute of War and Peace Studies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This event is IN PERSON&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BIO&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barbara F. Walter is a professor of political science and Rohr Chair in Pacific International Relations at the School and an adjunct professor in the UC San Diego Department of Political Science. She is an expert on international security, with an emphasis on civil wars. Her current research is on the behavior of rebel groups in civil wars, including inter-rebel group fighting, alliances and the strategic use of propaganda and extremism.She is the author of &lt;em&gt;How Civil Wars Start: And How to Stop Them.&lt;/em&gt;(New York: Penguian Random House)&lt;br /&gt;
Jan 11, 2022.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Walter received her Ph.D. in political science from the University of Chicago and completed postdoctoral research at the Olin Institute for Strategic Studies at Harvard University and at the Institute of War and Peace Studies at Columbia University. Walter is on the editorial board of the&lt;em&gt; American Political Science Review, International Organization, Journal of Politics, Journal of Conflict Resolution&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;International Studies Quarterly.&lt;/em&gt; She is also the recipient of numerous grants and fellowships, including awards from the National Science Foundation, Carnegie Corporation of New York, Harry Frank Guggenheim Foundation and Smith Richardson Foundation. Walter co-founded (with Erica Chenoweth) the blog&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="http://politicalviolenceataglance.org/"&gt;Political Violence @ A Glance&lt;/a&gt;, winner of numerous blogging awards since its inception in 2012. She holds a Ph.D and M.A. from the University of Chicago, and a B.A. from Bucknell College.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, please visit&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://www.barbarafwalter.com/"&gt;Barbara F. Walter&amp;rsquo;s personal site&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
