&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CeMeCA&amp;rsquo;s Regional Expert Paper Series: Making Expertise Accessible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us for the launch of the Center for Mexico and Central America&amp;rsquo;s new paper series. This interdisciplinary initiative partners with scholars and research institutes from Mexico, Central America, as well as the U.S. to make local knowledge and area studies expertise more broadly accessible. We will hear from the authors of our first paper &amp;ldquo;Conditions of Children in Guatemala&amp;rdquo; by Lauren Heidbrink, Sandra Chuc Norato, and Mar&amp;iacute;a Garc&amp;iacute;a Maldonado on the factors contributing to child migration from Guatemala.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
