&lt;p&gt;In this virtual conference, senior scholars and graduate students present research on&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Such Sweet Thunder&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;and related topics. Participants include NEA Jazz Master Delfeayo Marsalis, David Hajdu, professor at Columbia University Graduate School of Journalism and author of&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Lush Life: A Biography of Billy Strayhorn&lt;/em&gt;, Patricia Akhimie, Associate Professor of English at Rutgers University-Newark and author of&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Shakespeare and the Cultivation of Difference: Race and Conduct in the Early Modern World&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Routledge 2018), David Berger, composer, arranger, conductor, and Ellington authority, and Jack Chambers, Professor of Linguistics at the University of Toronto and author of&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Milestones: The Music and Times of Miles Davis&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Sweet Thunder: Duke Ellington&amp;#39;s Music in Nine Themes&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
